summaries.short: In the Season Three Finale, Nucky makes a deal with Rothstein as his war with Gyp Rosetti reaches its climax.
summaries.full: Season Three Finale. Desperate to weaken Gyp's alliance with Masseria and reclaim Atlantic City, Nucky cedes control of a prized asset to Rothstein. Harrow returns to Gillian's brothel for some unfinished business; Luciano is forced to take on a new heroin partner; Chalky and Capone team up; Margaret ends one relationship and considers resuming another.

summaries.short: (Season Four Premiere) Nucky brokers a peace; Atlantic City gets a new prohibition agent; Chalky opens a club; Richard reverts to his past.
summaries.full: (Season Four Premiere) Having survived his epic battle with Gyp Rosetti, Nucky makes a peace offering to Joe Masseria while working the odds with Arnold Rothstein. Chalky prepares to open the Onyx Club on the Boardwalk;a fresh-faced prohibition agent, Warren Knox, arrives in Atlantic City to learn the ropes; Richard Harrow returns to his violent ways.

summaries.short: Gyp makes his move in Atlantic City, forcing Nucky and Eddie to seek refuge with Chalky.
summaries.full: Gyp makes his move in Atlantic City, forcing Nucky and Eddie to seek refuge with Chalky. With the Artemis Club overrun by Rosetti thugs, Gillian contemplates a business future that includes an unwelcome partner. Luciano makes a deal he'll come to regret; Harrow loses his house privileges.

summaries.short: Chalky gets an unwanted partner; Van Alden muscles for Al Capone; J. Edgar Hoover introduces himself.
summaries.full: Now working as a delivery man for Dean O'Banion, Van Alden is ordered to keep tabs on Al Capone. Harlem gangster Dr. Valentin Narcisse arrives in Atlantic City, clashing with Chalky and Nucky. In Washington, Agent Knox aligns himself with J. Edgar Hoover. Harrow fails to finish a job in Milwaukee, while Eddie demands a promotion.

summaries.short: Nucky looks to silence foes in Washington and New York; Margaret envisions an alternate future.
summaries.full: Nucky reaches out to Gaston Means to keep Jess Smith quiet in Washington, and enlists Owen to neutralize Gyp's alliance with Joe Masseria in New York. Margaret considers an alternate future; Van Alden's side business backfires; Gyp fumes when a shipment comes up short; Harrow coerces an apology for Julia; Chalky sees opportunity in the ashes of a boardwalk institution.

summaries.short: Nucky invests in Tampa; Narcisse makes his mark at the Onyx Club; Harrow buries the past.
summaries.full: Nucky has reservations about investing in a Tampa land deal. While there, he befriends local speakeasy owner, Sally Wheet. Valentin Narcisse books a sexy jazz singer, Daughter Maitland, to perform at the Onyx. Willie, Eli's son, turns to Mickey Doyle and his bootleg warehouse to elevate his social standing in college. Harrow tries to bury his past.

summaries.short: A shaken Nucky tries to form a coalition against Gyp; a bootlegger's arrest turns up the heat on Daugherty.
summaries.full: Reeling from Gyp's most recent attack, Nucky vows to eliminate his nemesis through a coalition of familiar partners. In Washington, the arrest of a bootlegger puts Daugherty and Jess Smith on the hot seat. Emily gets a scaled-down birthday party; Gillian blames an absent Harrow for Tommy's latest misadventure; Gyp decides to buy a town's silence; Broadway mourns a fallen star.
